reviews.text: Local all-day breakfast. Open in the early morning and close late at night. A bowl of warm comfort porridge can wake you up to be ready for the rest of your day. The owner and staff are polite and very nice to all customers. Price is reasonable and a good choice for quick breakfast.
As a traveler, you can experience casual breakfast as local people. General and simple taste.  :-)

Coming from NYC, I had high expectations for a cha chan tang. With that said, I was a little disappointed with this small restaurant. I felt as though the food here was enough to satisfy my hunger, but not enough to blow me away. The congee was good, but the rice roll and the turnip cake was bland. Meh

Traditional porridge shop that's "the last Man standing" at Hau Fok Street. I have witnessed all the other shops changed hands and change trade.

There must be a reason why they can still survive.

My favourite is the traditional  "kap-dai-chok" (porridge with liver, stomach, tongue and a meat ball). Not everyone knows how to enjoy this but to the fans, this is good!

They have less adventurous selections too, they have at least 10 types of porridge to choose from, like minced beef or minced pork porridge. You can add an egg into your porridge if you like. 

Some locals like to order a porridge with a "soya sauce fried noodles" to go along. I find that a little too much carbs at one go.

They started as a porridge specialty shop, a few years ago, they serve noodles too.

A little pricey now but still good especially during winter 👍

Casual breakfast or light dining in a busy street. Many varieties of congee and fried noodles. Must try abalone congee 45 Hk$. Good value for money. Open very early for breakfast and closes late for supper. Service is very fast. Also provides English and Thai menu.

완탕면이 유명 한 홍콩 이라 가 봤더니 첨엔 간략한 메뉴판 주더니 관광객 인걸 파악 하고 그림 나와 있는 메뉴판 가져다 줌. 새우 완탕면 시켰더니 약 5분 정도 기다리니 가져다 줌... 맛 은... 일본 라멘 면발에 국물은 
새우육수 맛? 새우는 짰다... 전체적으로 왜 유명한건가 싶다... 더 맛난 집 이 있을 수 있겠으나 난 패스~

座位略微擁擠，建議在非用餐時段去
客人比員工多XD
餐點的 表現普普沒有格外出色，也不難吃
